 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of a topological graph consisting of edges and vertices.
     The edges may have associated length information.
     Additional vertices can be located on the edges with length in a defined distance from the start edge. 
     These additional vertices can be used to define sub-edges. 
     As needed the orientation of an edge can reversed. 
     Paths can be defined across the edges, oriented edges and sub-edges of the topological graph.  
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>the definition of a topological edge with a specified length;</li>
   <li>the definition of a vertex on an edge, that is positioned in a defined distance to the start of the edge;</li>
   <li>the representation of a single connected edge consisting of edges that may have length, paths across the connected edge set and vertices on the underlying edges;</li>
   <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="elemental_topology:1_scope">Elemental topology</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1005.</li>
 </inscope>

